title.narrative: OUTP 1.4: HEALTH EMERGENCY PREP. AND RESPONSE

description.narrative: Strengthened capacity for preparedness, implementation, coordination and monitoring of nutrition response targeting most vulnerable boys, girls and women in humanitarian situations, which contributes to Child Health, Child Health (Covid), Early Childhood Development, Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Outcome 1: Eighty per cent of pregnant women, new-borns, children and adolescents have equitable access to and utilize high-impact, cost-effective and quality health interventions and practice healthy behaviours by 2020
